title: St Martin-in-the-Fields (painting)
text:
St Martin-in-the-Fields is a painting of a child street vendor outside the church of <a href="St%20Martin-in-the-Fields">St Martin-in-the-Fields</a> in <a href="Trafalgar%20Square">Trafalgar Square</a>, London, painted by <a href="William%20Logsdail">William Logsdail</a> from 1888 in the collection of <a href="Tate%20Britain">Tate Britain</a>.
An engraving from the painting was published in "<a href="The%20Graphic">The Graphic</a>", 1894.
